        classCompatibility: `Thalren produce Animists naturally — the fog's memory-destruction demands that power be carved into permanent form rather than trusted to a mind. They produce Inquisitors because the Wyrd-horrors of the Frostwood are born directly from human fear, and someone must name them. Animists emerge from the Thalren tradition of speaking to the Mimir's preserved identities and ancestral spirits. Wardens arise from the archive-city's garrison tradition — Greymark has never been taken, and someone stays to ensure it stays that way.

Skald produce Berserkers first, Ironclad Martyrs second — two expressions of the same philosophical position about the body as a weapon. Augurs emerge from the glacier-tomb tradition: the dead stand upright in the ice, and the Skald have always known how to read what the preserved dead remember.

Tessen produce Wardens above all — what is a sealed keep but a territory defended by architecture and will? Spellguards emerge from the Tessen's paranoia about the Fexrick pipes they depend on. Harbingers are the predictable product of a culture that has been preparing for its own extinction for four centuries and keeps not dying. Revenants arise rarely but inevitably among the Tessen who cannot accept that their bloodline will end when the last person in the keep does.

Solvarn produce Martyrs first — the entire culture is a martyrdom, and the class formalizes what the Solvarn have been doing since House Solvan marched its heirs north. Pyrofiends emerge from those who made the obvious connection between Sol's residual heat and Scathrach's volcanic offer. Augurs arise from sun-priests who looked into the dying light too long. Harbingers emerge from the ones who looked away.

Merryn produce Gambit reflexively — the tradition was practically invented by the Merryn and then formalized after the fact. Shapers arise from shipboard combat, where rigid stance-work is lethal on a pitching deck. Minstrels carry the storm-rhythm tradition. Revenants emerge from Merryn who drowned and remember the Myrathil's breath on the other side.

Ordan produce Apex as a cultural baseline — the steppe requires predator-knowledge before anything else. Animists are the Ordan's spiritual tradition distilled to its core: instinct bonded with ancestral spirit-channeling. Minstrels carry the throat-song tradition in weaponized form. Gambit arise among those who notice that the migration always takes the path that costs the least — and begin to wonder if someone is adjusting the probability before the herd decides.

Morren produce Toxicologists because the Bryngloom's pharmacological resources are extraordinary and the Morren have centuries of incentive to understand what the bog produces. Revenants arise naturally in a community that lives adjacent to the Vreken's ancestral-spirit culture. Inquisitors are produced by those who eventually decide to stop being afraid of their Neth contracts and start dismantling them. Revenants also emerge among Morren who have renegotiated so many terms with the Keeper's adjacent power that they have begun to accidentally replicate the Neth's own partial death.`
